The Enterprise Code is provided under the Nodaro Sustainable Use
License with the following ADDITIONAL terms.

1. PRODUCTION USE REQUIRES SUBSCRIPTION
   Production use of the Enterprise Code requires a valid, paid
   subscription to Nodaro Cloud or Nodaro Enterprise. "Production use"
   means any deployment of the Software where ANY of the following
   are true:
   (a) the Software is accessible to end users (defined as any person
       other than the developer's personal evaluation team);
   (b) the Software generates real revenue, or is offered as part of a
       commercial product or service;
   (c) the Software processes real customer data, real production
       workloads, or production metrics;
   (d) the deployment includes any billing, credit, quota,
       subscription, or monetization features from the Enterprise Code.
   This applies regardless of the EDITION environment variable or any
   other configuration setting.

2. DEVELOPMENT AND TESTING EXCEPTION
   You may, at no cost, copy, modify, run, and study the Enterprise
   Code for development, testing, and evaluation purposes on
   non-production infrastructure, provided that:
   (a) the deployment is not accessible to end users beyond the
       developer's own evaluation team;
   (b) no real customer data, real revenue, or real production
       workloads are processed; and
   (c) the deployment uses only synthetic test accounts and data.

3. REDISTRIBUTION
   You may not distribute the Enterprise Code, in original or modified
   form, to third parties without a separate written agreement with
   Nodaro. This is true even if the recipients hold their own Nodaro
   subscriptions.

4. NO WHITE-LABEL OR REBRAND
   You may not modify, repackage, rebrand, or relicense the Enterprise
   Code (or any derivative work thereof) for distribution to third
   parties under any name other than "Nodaro," regardless of whether
   you hold a subscription. This includes but is not limited to:
   (a) creating a standalone product, service, or application that
       incorporates or is derived from the Enterprise Code;
   (b) reselling access to the Enterprise Code or modifications thereof;
   (c) offering the Enterprise Code as a white-label or private-label
       solution under a different brand name.

5. NO COMPETING SERVICE
   Even if you hold a valid Nodaro subscription, you may not:
   (a) create, operate, or fund a software product, platform, or
       service whose core functionality is substantially similar to
       Nodaro Cloud or Nodaro Enterprise (i.e., low-code/no-code
       workflow orchestration with node-based DAG composition, node
       libraries, and AI-mediated execution); or
   (b) license, sublicense, or resell Nodaro Cloud or Nodaro
       Enterprise functionality to third parties under a different
       brand or product name.

6. NO COMPETITIVE REIMPLEMENTATION
   You may not use the Enterprise Code, including by inspection, study,
   or processing through any automated tool (including but not limited
   to large language models, code-generation systems, or
   program-synthesis tools), to design, develop, or train a
   substantially similar system, where "substantially similar system"
   has the same scope as defined in Section 5(a) of this License.
   Reading the Enterprise Code for legitimate development, testing,
   evaluation, security research, or contribution to Nodaro itself
   remains permitted under the terms of this License and the root
   `LICENSE`.

7. NO AI TRAINING OR INFERENCE
   You may not use the Enterprise Code, in whole or in part, as:
   (a) training data, fine-tuning data, or evaluation data for any
       machine learning model, large language model, code-generation
       model, or program-synthesis system intended for public release
       or commercial use;
   (b) retrieval-augmented context, embedding source, or knowledge
       base for any such model;
   (c) input to any automated system whose output is intended to
       replicate, substitute for, or commercially compete with the
       Enterprise Code.
   Carve-outs:
   (i)   Personal AI assistants (including IDE coding assistants and
         chat interfaces) used by individual developers while
         legitimately contributing to Nodaro, evaluating Nodaro under
         Section 2, or operating Nodaro under a valid subscription are
         permitted, provided their outputs are used only for those
         purposes;
   (ii)  Code search, security scanning, vulnerability detection, and
         license compliance tools that process the Enterprise Code as
         part of a transient analysis pipeline (without retaining the
         code in a model) are permitted;
   (iii) Academic research that processes the Enterprise Code as part
         of a published scholarly work, provided the work does not
         release a derivative model trained on the Enterprise Code, is
         permitted.

8. PATENT TERMINATION
   If any party initiates patent litigation against Nodaro or any
   licensee (including a cross-claim or counterclaim) alleging that
   the Enterprise Code or a contribution thereto infringes any patent,
   all patent rights granted under this License or the root `LICENSE`
   to the initiating party for the Enterprise Code shall terminate as
   of the date such litigation is filed.

